snippets.title:
Delete one document using MongoDB CRUD operations in 
    Atlas Functions
snippets.description:
You can delete a single document by performing 
    MongoDB CRUD operations using an Atlas Function. Pass the
    objectID as an argument to the Atlas Function, and use 
    'deleteOne' in the Function context.

snippets.title:
Insert one document using MongoDB CRUD operations in 
    Atlas Functions
snippets.description:
You can insert a single document by performing 
    MongoDB CRUD operations using an Atlas Function. Pass the 
    arguments to the Atlas Function, and use 'insertOne' in the Function context.
